{"body": "Triage:

(a) Root cause: The exponential backoff counter is held in worker-local memory and is not persisted/restored across worker process recycles. When a worker recycles (which happens more frequently under load), the counter resets to zero, so any worker experiencing a recycle re-enters the retry loop at the minimum backoff interval. During an upstream 5xx storm this produces a synchronized burst of full-speed retries from all recycled workers simultaneously (thundering herd) instead of a gradually increasing, spread-out retry pattern.

(b) Priority: P1 — This doesn't cause an outright outage by itself, but it actively defeats the purpose of backoff during exactly the scenario it's meant to protect against (upstream instability), risking amplification of downstream incidents and self-inflicted overload. Needs fixing soon but isn't a live active-fire (P0) unless it's currently causing an ongoing incident.", "issue_id": "issue-1"}

{"body": "Triage:

(a) Root cause: When the event queue backs up beyond ~500 items (observed at 1k events/min load), the retry buffer holding not-yet-delivered alert events does not get flushed before the worker process recycles. Because the buffer is in-memory and tied to the worker's lifecycle, any events still sitting in it at recycle time are silently lost, accounting for the observed 3-5% drop rate. This is closely related to the worker-recycle handling issue seen in the retries ticket — the buffer needs to either flush synchronously before recycle or persist state externally.

(b) Priority: P0 — Silent, unrecoverable data loss of user-facing alerts (3-5% under moderate load) is a correctness/reliability failure with no workaround for the end user; this should be fixed immediately.", "issue_id": "issue-2"}

{"body": "Triage:

(a) Root cause: Not a bug — this is a feature gap. The migration CLI currently has no mode to compute and display the planned schema diff without executing it, so there's no way to review changes in CI prior to hitting staging.

(b) Priority: P2 — Valuable for safety/review workflow but purely additive with existing (manual) workarounds available (e.g., reviewing migration files directly), so it can be scheduled as normal feature work.", "issue_id": "issue-3"}
